        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 30 at 2:40PM CDT by NWS Northern Indiana</headline>
        <description>At 240 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Knox, moving east at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Knox, Hamlet, Thomaston, Brems, and English Lake.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
